 <h2>
  <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">
   Overview
  </span>
  <span class="mw-editsection">
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    [
   </span>
   <a class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">
    edit
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-divider">
    |
   </span>
   <a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=ITOM_Container_Deployment_Foundation:2019.05/WhitepaperMonitoring&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">
    edit source
   </a>
   <span class="mw-editsection-bracket">
    ]
   </span>
  </span>
 </h2>
 <p>
  Systems that run Docker and Kubernetes can be monitored in various ways.
 </p>
 <p>
  Docker provides basic runtime metrics through the use of “docker stats”.
 </p>
 <p>
  See
  <a class="external free" href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/admin/runmetrics/" rel="nofollow" target="1">
   https://docs.docker.com/engine/admin/runmetrics/
  </a>
  .
 </p>
 <p>
  In the CDF, monitoring occurs at the Kubernetes level.
 </p>
 <p>
  The monitoring data is collected from Docker by cAdvisor which acts as an abstraction layer for particular container runtime engines.
 </p>
 <p>
  The CDF includes Heapster and Metrics Server for cluster-wide monitoring. Both talk directly to Kubernetes metrics endpoints where the raw data is provided by the Kubelet.
 </p>
 <p>
  The Kubelet gets this information from cAdvisor.
 </p>
 <p>
  The Kubelet information is then aggregated by Heapster/Metrics Server and visualized via the Kubernetes dashboard.
 </p>
 <p>
  See
  <a class="external free" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/resource-usage-monitoring/" rel="nofollow" target="1">
   https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/cluster-administration/resource-usage-monitoring/
  </a>
  ;
  <a class="external free" href="https://github.com/kubernetes/heapster" rel="nofollow" target="1">
   https://github.com/kubernetes/heapster
  </a>
  ;
  <a class="external free" href="https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/resource-metrics-pipeline/" rel="nofollow" target="1">
   https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/debug-application-cluster/resource-metrics-pipeline/
  </a>
 </p>
